BASE: In saucepan, heat corn syrup, margarine, brown sugar, peanut butter, and chocolate chips. Remove from heat; stir in nuts and cereal. Using lightly buttered spatula, press into buttered 3.5 L (13 x 9-inch) pan. TOPPING: In a small saucepan, gently heat peanut butter and chocolate chips. When melted, blend and spread over base. Refrigerate until firm. Cut into squares.